Build Notes for llvmtools

To avoid contamination from host, the bare minimum will be cross-compiled and the rest under chroot.  All packages should be installed in llvmtools.

An example of contamination is building vim. It will try to link against host's xorg libraries.

Cross-compiled:
o Musl libc
o Kernel Headers
o libexecinfo
o ncurses
o LLVM
o m4
o Bash
o coreutils
o diffutils
o findutils
o gawk
o Grep
o gzip
o Make
o patch
o sed
o tar
o xz-utils
o GCC (optional?)
o Libstdc++ (optional?)

Compiled under chroot
o gettext-tiny
o bison
o perl
o python3
o texinfo
o util-linux
o cmake
o Samurai/Ninja
o vim/nano (optonal)
o tcl (optional)
o expect (optional)
o dejaGNU (optional)
o libtree (optional, good for troubleshooting)
o package manager (optional, remonder, out-of-scope)
